Master's in Business Administration from EOI in Madrid.Mr. Bermejo is based in Nairobi.






Mariel Crisostomo - Financial Controller - Projects
Mariel is a Certified Accountant in the Philippines with Master's Degree in Business Administration.She has more than 15 years of experience in various facets of Finance including Audit, Management Accounting, Financial Analysis & Reporting, Taxation, Treasury & Controllership. She gained her audit experience at PKF Philippines (RS Bernaldo & Associates) and was seconded at Grant Thornton Vietnam. She worked as a Financial Controller for Drug Store Chains, Financial Holding & Investments Company and concurrent volunteer work for Charitable & Educational Foundations. She also served as a Financial Analyst for Standard Bank PLC SPVs in the Philippines.Mariel is an advocate of continuing process & systems development and deeply believes in empowering people to achieve efficiency at work.Mariel is based in Manila.






Axel Gnassounou - Project Engineer - AREF
                            Mr. Gnassounou has experience in renewable energy projects across Europe and Africa. He is currently involved into engineering, due diligence, and project management of AREF projects.Mr. Gnassounou is on secondment to Berkeley Energy from the African Biofuel and Renewable Energy Company where he held a Project Officer position on projects in all 8 WAEMU countries and in Chad. He previously worked for solar developers in designing, planning and delivering renewable energy projects.Mr. Gnassounou holds a BEng in renewables energy (University of Montpellier) and a Master's degree in Project Management (EI.CESI).Mr. Gnassounou is based in Nairobi.
                        





 Dan Gonzales - Philippines Legal Counsel - REAF and REAF II
Mr. Gonzales is the Philippines Legal Counsel for Berkeley Energy, responsible for providing legal support to the growing portfolio of Philippine projects and to REAF and REAF II generally. He acts as the corporate secretary for Philippines investment and holding companies, manages corporate governance practices and provides general transaction and corporate support for REAF and REAF II.Before joining Berkeley in 2016, Mr. Gonzales had nine years of experience as a lawyer in the Philippines specialising in the natural resources industry and renewable energy sector. He worked for PetroEnergy Resources Corporation, a publicly listed Philippines company, for over five years where he was responsible for handling various corporate, legal, contractual and regulatory issues and requirements of PetroEnergy's renewable energy projects.Mr. Gonzales holds a Bachelor of Science degree in Geology and a Bachelor of Laws, both from the University of the Philippines.Mr. Gonzales is based in Manila.






Ian Griffiths - Project Director - REAF and REAF II
Mr. Griffiths has 15+ years of experience in managing multidisciplinary teams in the development, construction and operation renewable energy and waste management assets in the UK and Australia. He is a member of the investment committee for REAF.Mr. Griffiths has a strong operational and contract management background and has held management positions in Waste Recycling Group, working with Mr. Kundi and Mr. Renfrew, in the UK, Boral Australia and Tox Free Australia.Prior to joining Berkeley Energy, Mr. Griffiths lived and worked in the remote Pilbara region of Australia in the capacity of technical projects manager and latterly business development manager. Mr Griffiths was responsible for supporting a portfolio of blue chip mining and LNG clients in a challenging geographic setting, during a period of unprecedented growth in the resources sector.Mr. Griffiths has a BSc (Hons) from the University of Wales and is based in the Berkeley Energy Singapore office.






David Hastings - Project Director - AREF
                            Mr. Hastings is responsible for the due diligence, engineering, procurement and project management of AREF investments.Mr. Hastings has 25+ years of development, engineering, construction and operations experience in the major infrastructure and renewable energy industries, across Europe, North America, South America, Australia and Asia. He has held a variety of senior management technical, commercial, contractual and operational roles for contractors, developers, owner operators and consultants and has a strong track record of primary responsibility for over 20 operating wind power projects, as well as having experience in energy storage, geothermal, solar, hydro and biomass technologies. Mr. Hastings holds a BEng with Distinction from Dundee Institute of Technology.Mr. Hastings is based in Nairobi.






